headline.main: SOVIET MAY LAUNCH A SPACESHIP TODAY

results.snippet: MOSCOW, Oct. 11 (UPI) -- The Soviet Union will launch the first passenger spaceship in history within the next few days, possibly tomorrow, informed sources said today.

headline.main: U.S. SPACE TRIPS MAY END ON LAND; Agency is Weighing Plan to Emulate Soviet Feat

results.snippet: BALTIMORE, Oct. 28 -- Space agency officials are "seriously considering" a proposal to match the Soviet feat of landing a manned space vehicle on land rather than water.
